Title: Maritime Performance Analytics & Sea-Route Risk Assessment System for Ships/Submarines
1. Project Overview
The Maritime Performance Analytics & Sea-Route Risk Assessment System is a comprehensive data analytics project designed to analyze ship and submarine operational performance using multi-source maritime datasets.
The project integrates navigation logs, environmental conditions, fuel consumption data, and maintenance records to evaluate vessel efficiency, fuel usage, weather impact, sea-route risks, and operational delays.
This project focuses purely on Data Analytics and Statistical Modeling, without mandatory machine learning, and provides actionable insights through visual dashboards.
2. Objectives
•	Clean and preprocess multi-source maritime datasets
•	Integrate navigation, fuel, environmental, and maintenance data
•	Analyze ship and submarine performance metrics
•	Evaluate fuel consumption and engine efficiency
•	Assess weather impact on navigation and delays
•	Identify high-risk sea routes
•	Analyze submarine depth vs speed efficiency
•	Build an interactive dashboard for maritime insights
3. Dataset Details
The project uses multiple cleaned datasets merged into a unified master table.
Key Datasets:
•	Ship Specifications Dataset
•	Navigation Logs Dataset
•	Environmental Conditions Dataset
•	Fuel Consumption Logs
•	Maintenance & Incident Logs
Master Dataset:
maritime_master_dataset.csv
Important Columns:
•	vessel_id
•	vessel_type
•	speed_knots
•	fuel_used_lph
•	distance_nm
•	depth_m
•	wave_height_m
•	wind_speed_knots
