•	course_deviation_deg
•	maintenance_type
•	incident_type
4. Data Cleaning Steps
•	Removal of duplicate records
•	Handling missing values using forward-fill methods
•	Standardizing timestamp and coordinate formats
•	Validating numerical ranges (speed, depth, fuel)
•	Separating submarine-specific depth data
•	Saving cleaned datasets into processed folder
5. Feature Engineering
The following analytical features were created:
•	Nautical Miles per Liter
•	Fuel Efficiency Score
•	Engine Health Score
•	Vessel Utilization Rate
•	Depth-Speed Efficiency Index (Submarines)
•	Environmental Delay Hours
•	Sea-Route Risk Score
•	Risk Category (Low / Medium / High)
6. Analytical Models (Non-ML)
Fuel Efficiency Model
•	Measures distance traveled per unit fuel
•	Normalized efficiency score (0–100)
Engine Health Model
•	Based on RPM variance and maintenance frequency
Delay Impact Model
•	Weather-based delay estimation using wave height, wind speed, storm probability
Sea-Route Risk Model
•	Composite risk score using environmental and navigation indicators
Depth-Speed Efficiency Model (Submarines)
•	Evaluates optimal underwater operational depths
7. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Key analyses performed:
•	Vessel speed vs wave height
•	Fuel consumption vs load weight
•	Submarine depth vs speed trends
•	Weather impact on route deviation
•	Maintenance frequency by vessel type
•	Risk-prone sea corridor identification
•	Correlation heatmaps of numerical variables
Generated visualizations include:
•	Bar charts
•	Histograms
•	Heatmaps
•	Bubble charts
•	Line graphs
8. Dashboard
A Streamlit-based interactive dashboard was developed to:
•	Display vessel KPIs
•	Visualize fuel consumption trends
•	Analyze depth vs speed for submarines
•	Monitor sea-route risk levels
•	Compare performance across vessel types
